Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of forty-two (42) months.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision, consecutive to the sentences presently being served.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) No contact with the victim, William Dorman or his family;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) obtain GED or HSED;
7) maintain absolute sobriety.
Minutes.
